Territory of Washington County of Lincoln} ss Territory of Washington vs. S.P. White Sheriff Court Bill in the above entitled case. I hereby certify that by virtue of a committment which is hereto anulled. I received the above named defendant into my custody in the sixth day of January A.D. 1885 and I further certify that on the tenth day of February AD 1885 I received a writ of Habeas Corpus filed that of the Disctrict Court of Fourth Judicial District of Washington Territory, and that I answered said writ recording to the command therein, and the said writ was held according to the papers filed herewith. And I forthwith certify that I was ordered by prosecuting atty. S.C. Hyde to without subpoenaas all persons knowing anything about the case be in attendance and live evidence in the trial of said writ of Habeas Corpus. The following is a correct account of all papers and prosecute. Served by me in the above entitles case. First to guarding prisoner 45 day from January 6th to Feb 16th at two dollars per nine $90.00 Boarding and lodging prisoner forty five days at $1.00 $45.00 Notifying the following named. Wtinesses to appear before his honor. Judge Turner at chambers in the city of Spokane Lincoln County W.T. on the 13th day of February A.D. 1885 by order of S.C. Hyde Pros. Atty. at the trial of the writ of habeas corpus in the within entitled case. Names Josiah, Cole, AJ Rogers, SA Porteh, JH Porteh, C.J. Brindle, Jeran K. Bearden, H.S. Bearden, J.S. Bearden, Witnesses for the territory Eight names at 40 ct. each 3.20 mileage from Spokane to Brint and return one hundred, and fifty mileage in notifying up witness one hundred total mileage two hundred and fifty mileout 10ct per mile 25.00 notifying witnesses for defence five at 40ct each 2.00 Same mileage as above and hereby charged one day in work in preparing rooms. to hold. court $3.00 one days attend once on 3.00 serving writ of Habeas Corpus 1.00 Committment 1.00 transporting prisoner from Spokane cty. Lincoln co. W.T. to Yakima County W.T. Two hundred and twenty five miles 22.50 Prisoner have on RailRoad 16.00 two days in Coveying Prisoner to jail at 6.00
Prisoner board three days at 1.00 per day 3.00 total cost of sheriff $24670 less 26.00 22070 25.00 Territory of Washington 24670 24570 County of Lincoln 2500 2500 27170 070 I john Cody Sheriff of Lincoln county Washington Territory do hereby certify that the above bill of cost are just and the charges made therein are according to statute and that I was instructed by the prosecuting S.C. Hyde. to file the same in the above for me. Within the other papers filed here with. John Cody dated at Spokane Lincoln County W.T. this 16th day of February A.D. 1885
